description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered nurse with current or previous critical care or HDU experience?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge and an opportunity to work as part of the nursing team, at one of the leading NHS Foundation Trusts in the UK?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced, enthusiastic nurses who are keen to help us deliver the best in care to our patients and their relatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the UHB In House Staff Bank Service, known as UHB+, we are able to offer you flexibility to choose when you work (subject to shift availability) and offer a variety of clinical areas including critical care, across different sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our commitment to you , as a member of our UHB Team , we will provide full training when you commence your employment with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional benefits include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay and conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full statutory/mandatory training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Corporate and Clinical Induction programme over 5 days and additional 5 day specific critical care induction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Membership of the NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about this exciting opportunity, please email: uhbplusrecruitmentandretention@uhb.nhs.uk or Alison.pratt@uhb.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
